## Example 1 — Divide a Polynomial by a Monomial

Find:

`(24a^4b^3 + 18a^2b^2 - 30ab^3)(6ab)^-1`

Rewrite as a fraction:

`(24a^4b^3 + 18a^2b^2 - 30ab^3) / (6ab)`

Split the quotient:

`= (24a^4b^3)/(6ab) + (18a^2b^2)/(6ab) - (30ab^3)/(6ab)`

Simplify:

`= 4a^3b^2 + 3ab - 5b^2`

